1. HashMapIterateandSearchKey
Easy
100 points
• 130 min suggested
Problem Description
1) Write a program to iterate keys & values of HashMap and also check given key exist or not? if exist then display the value of given key.

Examples
Example 1
Input:
Enter key to search:
102
Output:
HashMap Elements:
Key: 101, Value: Java
Key: 102, Value: Python
Key: 103, Value: C++

Key found!
Value of key 102 is: Python
Explanation:
HashMap stores data in the form of key–value pairs. entrySet() is used to iterate both keys and values together. containsKey() checks whether a specific key exists in the HashMap. If the key is found, get(key) is used to retrieve the value of that key.



import java.util.*;

public class Test{
    public static void main(String args[]){
        
        HashMap <Integer,String> map = new HashMap<>();

        map.put(101,"Java");
        map.put(102,"Python");
        map.put(103,"C++");

        int num = Integer.parseInt(IO.readln());
        IO.println("HashMap Elements:");
        map.forEach((k,v) -> IO.println("Key: "+ k+", Value: "+v));

        IO.println(" ");
        map.forEach((k,v) ->{
            if(num == k){
                IO.println("Key found!"); 
                IO.println("Value of key "+k+ " is: "+v);  
            }

        } 
        );


    }
}




